'''Trevor Doornbusch''' (born 6 July 1999) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for {{Dutch football updater|VVVVenlo}} club [[VVV-Venlo]]. Born in the Netherlands, he plays for the [[Curaçao national football team|Curaçao national team]].

==Club career==
Doornbusch is a product of the youth academies of [[SV Overbos|Overbos]], [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]], [[:de:RKSV RODA '23|RKSV RODA '23]], and [[SC Heerenveen|Heerenveen]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.trevordoornbusch.nl/|title=Trevor Doornbusch|website=Op weg naar de Top!}}</ref> He began his senior career with [[SC Heerenveen|Heerenveen]] in 2017, where he acted as their backup goalkeeper. On 5 April 2018, he signed his first professional contract with Heerenveen until 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://lc.nl/sport/Trevor-Doornbusch-tekent-contract-bij-SC-Heerenveen-23064226.html|title=Trevor Doornbusch tekent contract bij SC Heerenveen|website=Leeuwarder Courant}}</ref> He transferred to [[SC Telstar|Telstar]] in the summer of 2020, and had a controversial stint where he played some games, lost his starting spot, and eventually reclaimed the position.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.noordhollandsdagblad.nl/cnt/dmf20211112_16148558|title=Fel bekritiseerde doelman Trevor Doornbusch laat zich niet gek maken door tegenslagen: ’Je kunt het maar beter omdraaien. Als je ermee gaat zitten, wordt het zwaar’|website=www.noordhollandsdagblad.nl}}</ref> On 3 August 2022, he transferred to [[FC Dordrecht|Dordrecht]] where he was again the reserve goalkeeper.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rtvdordrecht.nl/nieuws/trevor-doornbusch-en-jeugdige-baltussen-vullen-keepersposities-fc-dordrecht-in|title=Trevor Doornbusch en jeugdige Baltussen vullen keepersposities FC Dordrecht in|website=www.rtvdordrecht.nl}}</ref>

On 27 February 2025, Doornbusch signed a two-and-a-half-season contract with [[VVV-Venlo]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=VVV-Venlo|url=https://www.vvv-venlo.nl/nieuws/vvv-venlo-contracteert-doelman-trevor-doornbusch-tot-medio-2027|title=VVV-Venlo contracteert doelman Trevor Doornbusch tot medio 2027|trans-title=VVV-Venlo signs goalkeeper Trevor Doornbusch until mid-2027|date=27 February 2025|access-date=8 March 2025|language=nl}}</ref>

==International career==
Born in the Netherlands, Doornbusch is of Curaçaoan descent. He is a former youth international for the Netherlands, having played up to the [[Netherlands national under-18 football team|Netherlands U18]]s.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ajaxshowtime.com/index.php/bijzaken-en-geruchten/ajax-hofleverancier-bij-oefenstage-oranje-o18|title=Ajax hofleverancier bij oefenstage Oranje O18|date=6 April 2017|website=Ajax Showtime}}</ref> He was called up to the [[Curaçao national football team|Curaçao national team]] for a set of matches in March 2023.<ref>{{Cite web| last = Bomgaars| first = Arco| title = Doelman FC Dordrecht na trip met Curaçao: ‘Ik heb Messi toch maar mooi live van dichtbij zien spelen’| work = [[Algemeen Dagblad]]| access-date = 5 November 2023| date = 1 April 2023| url = https://www.ad.nl/regiosport-dordrecht/doelman-fc-dordrecht-na-trip-met-curacao-ik-heb-messi-toch-maar-mooi-live-van-dichtbij-zien-spelen~adf8c15e/| language = nl}}</ref>
On 14 July 2023, Doornbush made his debut for Curaçao in a friendly against Puerto Rico in Miami, resulting in a draw (0–0).

